<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 45.37 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday closed at 3433.21 as
against the last close of 3387.84, netting a gain of 45.37 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index rose by 24.23 points to 1533.54 from the
previous close of 1509.31.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted sharply up at
352.73 and 138.11 compared with last weekend close of 346.78 and
135.78 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities fluctuated widely and posted a record turnover on the
opening day of the new account on the stock market here Monday in
the wake of brisk purchases from foreign institutional investors
and domestic funds alternated heavy selling by domestic
institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
