<HEADLINE> Philippine Farm Output to Grow 2.5-3.5 Percent: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine agriculture
sector is expected to post a positive growth of 2.5-3.5 percent
this year, a senior government official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sufficient rains and other favorable factors enabled the
farmers to plant large tracts of land with rice, corn, vegetables
and other crops, Agriculture Secretary William Darin said at a
meeting of provincial governors and government officials on food
security.
</P>
<P>
"We expect surplus rice production in the first quarter of
1999," Dar said.
</P>
<P>
He urged all concerned sectors and provincial governors to give
their hands on the country's food security.
</P>
<P>
The country's agriculture sector suffered a slump last year,
the worst in the last 30 years, due mainly to the devastating
effects of the El Nino and La Nina weather phenomena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
