<HEADLINE> German Industrial Production Slips Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Latest data showed a slowdown
underway in German industry, with November manufacturing output
falling 2.5 per cent from October, Bonn reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry said that the downturn included a 6.5 per
cent fallout in production by energy suppliers.
</P>
<P>
In two-month comparisons to compensate for short-term
fluctuations, German industrial output in the October-November
period was down one per cent from the preceding August-September
time frame. But the level was 2.2 per cent higher than in
October-November 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
