<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Relatives of Former Afghan Governor Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The deceased were close relatives of former governor of
Ningarhar (Afghanistan) Haji Abdul Qadeer.
</P>
<P>
"It seems the murderers were very specific and knew what to
do," Superintendent of Police Urban Rehmatullah Khan told Xinhua
by telephone.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the intruders took away no valuables from the
residence of Abdul Haq Qadeer explains that they were not thieves,
Rehmatullah said, adding only investigations will unravel the
facts.
</P>
<P>
According to details, some armed persons sneaked into Haq's
residence located in phase 4 of Hayatabad town. The assailants
opened indiscriminate fires on the sleeping inmates of the house.
</P>
<P>
"It may be the result of their blood feud with another Afghan
commander," said another high police official when contacted.
However, the Haqs are tight-lipped over the killings.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, commander Haq was associated with Hezb-e-Islami of
Yunas Khalis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
