<DOCNO> XIE19990112.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Produces New Fighter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Russian air force will have
MiG corporation's latest product, a multipurpose attack jet
fighter, Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev announced on
Tuesday, according to the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
At a presentation show in the town of Zhukovsky outside Moscow
Sergeyev said the new plane excels all Russian planes and is not
inferior to the most advanced Western models, including the latest
American D-22A Raptor fighter.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the work on the newly-designed fighter
normally lasts for five to seven years. At least one billion
rubles (about 50 million U.S. dollars) will have to be invested in
flight tests. The first flights are to be carried out at the end
of February 1999.
</P>
<P>
MiG corporation's general director Mikhail Korzhuyev said that
the new fighter is difficult to be detected by radar and is
extremely maneuverable which creates new opportunities for
enhancing the efficiency of the latest weapons systems.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev said that the modernization of MiG-29 fighters (MiG-
29SMT and Mig-UBT variants) will constitute the bulk of the
program for the development of the Russian air force intended for
the period until 2005.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax quoted him as saying that the development of
strategic aviation, a component of the Russian nuclear forces,
will also be based on upgrading planes, primarily the Tu-160
strategic bombers, and on the utilization of the latest weapons
systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
