<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwestern Chinese Airport Resumes Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Kunming airport, in the
capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, resumed operation
this morning after having been closed for a day because of a
heavy snowfall.
</P>
<P>
At 11:14 a.m., a flight from Kunming to Xishuangbanna was able
to leave the airport thanks to the runway-clearing work of
airport staff and the warming temperatures.
</P>
<P>
The snow started falling early yesterday morning and piled up
by 8:00 o'clock so that the airport had to be closed. More than
50 flights were canceled and 5,000 passengers were delayed.
</P>
<P>
Today, 120 airplanes will have taken off and most of the
stranded passengers will be able to leave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
