<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Congratulates Nazarbayev on Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
congratulated Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev Tuesday
on his "sound victory in the January 10 presidential elections,"
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a phone call to Nazarbayev, Yeltsin said that Kazakhstan
will remain Russia's sincere friend and reliable partner, and an
active advocate of broader and deeper cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed bilateral relations and
contacts in the Interstate Council of the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yegor Stroyev, Speaker of the Upper House of the
Russian parliament and Chairman of the Council of the CIS
Inter-parliamentary Assembly also congratulated Nazarbayev on his
re-election, saying that it ensures "Kazakhstan's stable
development in the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev led Kazakhstan during the Soviet era and became the
republic's president after its independence in 1991. According to
the April 1995 referendum, He will end his presidency in 2000.
</P>
<P>
However, the Kazakh parliament revised the constitution in
October last year and decided to hold the election ahead of
time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
