<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Step up Tax Collection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China set the quota for its
tax revenues for 1999 at a national work conference on taxation
that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Jin Renqing, director of the State Taxation Administration,
said at the conference that tax revenues must at least grow by
6.4 percent this year over the base number to 946 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
He urged taxation departments at all levels to use all
possible legal means in tax collection to make sure that this
year's target will be met.
</P>
<P>
"Tax revenues are the lifeline of our country," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that efforts must be redoubled to crack down on tax
evasions and fraud in export refunding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
