<HEADLINE> Three People Suspected Of Smuggling Returned To China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Three people who were
suspected of smuggling and fraud and fled China to avoid
prosecution have been repatriated, the Ministry of Public
Security reported today.
</P>
<P>
Cui Zhiyi, the general manager of a Tianjin foreign trade
corporation, and Guo Yufei, a manager with the company, obtained
11 million yuan (about 1.3 million U.S. dollars) through fraud in
foreign trade from January 1995 to May 1996, and fled the country
in February, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Police in Jiangsu Province also got a local businessman, Lu
Bin, returned from overseas last November. Lu ran a company in
the city of Zhangjiagang in Jiangsu and was found to have
smuggled cars and forged automobile documents from 1994 to 1998.
He ran away to avoid paying several million yuan worth of taxes.
His case is still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
