<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Businesses Growing In South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 industrial output of
overseas-funded businesses in this special economic zone,
Guangdong Province, rose 10.9 percent over the 1997 figures to
127.3 billion yuan, contributing to Shenzhen's 14.5 percent
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released at a press conference here
today, last year contractual investment by overseas enterprises
in Shenzhen grew 55.2 percent over 1997 to 2.75 billion US
dollars, with the actual use of overseas investment reaching 1.6
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export by overseas businesses also maintained a strong
momentum in 1998, accounting for nearly 60 percent of the
Shenzhen's total export volume of 26.4 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local tax officials said that the taxes paid by overseas e
nterprises have kept growing in recent years, and in 1998, their
taxes reached 3.2 billion yuan, accounting for more than 25
percent of the total taxes collected by Shenzhen local taxation
bureau.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen has 13,000 overseas-funded enterprises, with 16.9
billion US dollars in actual investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
