<HEADLINE> One Third Beijing Households to Buy Houses One Third Beijing Households to Buy Houses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A sample survey made by
Beijing Statistics Bureau indicated that 36 percent of Beijing
households prepare to buy houses.
</P>
<P>
Today's Beijing Economic Daily reported that the survey, made
among 820 households in Beijing's 18 districts and counties,
showed that most of Beijing households plan to buy
government-subsidized houses.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicated that 34.51 percent of Beijing households
have already bought houses and 7.8 percent of them would like to
buy more houses.
</P>
<P>
Among the urban districts, Haidian witnesses much more
households who are ready to buy government-subsidized houses. A
total of 42 percent of the surveyed households in the district
are to buy the low-priced houses.
</P>
<P>
Most of Haidian residents are teachers of universities and
employees in research institutions who are able to afford the
government-subsidized houses.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicated that among households ready to buy
houses in Pinggu and Yanqing counties, more households plan to
buy commercial houses, whose prices are much higher than the
government subsidized houses.
</P>
<P>
So far, most of Beijing households rent houses from their
units at a quite low price and a number of households keep
wait-and-see altitude to the government's housing reform which no
longer allow residents to rent newly-built houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
