<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Parini Wins World Cup Giant Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- World Cup leader Margerita Parini
kept her cool in trying conditions to win the giant slalom gold
medal at the the snowboarding world championships in
Berchtesgaden, Germany on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Italian Parini, who won two races on the World Cup circuit
this winter, underlined her dominance in heavy snow by clocking a
winning combined time of two minutes 18.51 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Holder Sondra van Ert of the United States, who led after the
first leg, had to be content with silver in 2:19.24 while Lidia
Tretter completed a successful day for Italy by taking bronze in
2:20.10.
</P>
<P>
Poor visibility on the Goetschen piste led to mistakes by many
of the leading contenders.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Karine Ruby of France dropped out of
contention on the first leg when she lost her balance on the
upper part of the course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
