<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 79.99 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 79.99 points to
3353.22 as against Monday's close of 3433.21.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost by 37.36 points to 1496.18 as
against the previous close of 1533.54.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted lower at 344.90
and 135.11 compared with the last close of 352.73 and 138.11
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities suffered a sharp setback on the BSE market Tuesday on
profittaking by leading operators and a technical correction to
over bought positions.
</P>
<P>
Foreign institutional investors had restricted their activity
and supported only a few equities. The domestic funds were net
sellers for squaring up positions in some scrips. 
</P>
