<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies from HK Continue Visit in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to the Ninth
National People's Congress from the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) visited the Guangzhou Economic
Development Zone and Guangzhou High-Tech Development Zone today.
</P>
<P>
They highly praised the achievements scored by two high-tech
companies and put forward a number of suggestions on promoting
the development of China's high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Philip Wang, a Hong Kong deputy, said China has a great number
of software engineers. If they are organized efficiently, Chinese
products will be quite competitive on the world market as
production costs in china are much lower than in other countries.
</P>
<P>
Wilfred Wong called on the government to give energetic
support to high-tech enterprises and set up a risk investment
fund for high-tech development.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan said China should pay attention to the training of
financial and business managers.  
</P>
