<HEADLINE> Overwhelming Shen/Zhao Stamp Dominance in Pairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, Jilin Province, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Olympic
fifth-placed Shen Xue and Zhao Hongbo from Harbin stamped their
overwhelming dominance on the domestic ice as they triumphed in
the figure skating pairs event Tuesday at the China's Winter
Games.
</P>
<P>
The six-year pairs, who finished fourth in the Goodwill Games
in the United States last August, skated flawlessly in the
soundtrack of the Disney picture Mulan, with the vocal audience
responsing to every jump through the performance.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not quite satisfied with myself," Zhao said, "but my
partner, Shen Xue, had a wonderful night."
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Zhao, who concentrated on pairs ten years ago,
partnered with Shen in 1993 and won their first international
title in the NHK World Cup competition in Japan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In the Nagano Winter Olympics last Feburary, they finished
fifth, the ever-best result in the event for the Asians in the
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Dan and Zhang Hao, new champions of Harbin in a World
Cup event in Beijing in 1998, overcame teammates Pang Qing and
Tong Hao to take the silver medals. Pang and Tong finished third
after they failed to make some jumps Tuesday night in the Five
Rings Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Three figure skating gold medals, men's and women's singles
and ice dancing, will come out Wednesday night when Olympics
fifth-placer Guo Zhengxin is seeking to prove his fame in the
free program. Guo trailed Li Chengjiang from Changchun at second
after the short program in men's singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
