<HEADLINE> Botwinov Beats Daehlie to Win 30-km Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Austria's Mikhail Botwinov
overtook multiple Olympic champion Bjoern Daehlie in the dying
stages to win a 30-km freestyle cross-country skiing World Cup
race in Nove Mesto, the Czech Republic on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Botwinov trailed Norway's Daehlie until two kilometers from
home. He beat his rival by just 1.3 seconds after finishing in
one hour 19 minutes 10.5 seconds.
</P>
<P>
However Daehlie, who won Saturday's 15-km classic race,
remains well clear at the top of the World Cup standings with 560
points.
</P>
<P>
Victory put Botwinov in third place on 336 points, 52 behind
Sweden's Mathias Fredriksson, who finished sixth.
</P>
<P>
Estonia's Kristina Smigun scored her first World Cup victory
of the season, winning the women's 15-km freestyle in 42 minutes
41.5 seconds from Italy's Stefania Belmondo.
</P>
<P>
Norway's Bente Martinsen, winner of Saturday's 10-km classic
race, stayed top of the standings despite finishing 14th. 
</P>
