equipment, the 8th exhibition of decorative lamps and chandeliers,
the 8th exhibition of ceramics, porcelain and glass, the 9th
exhibition of detergents, hygienic and cosmetic products and the
8th exhibition of home and office decoration and furniture.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Egyptian Minister of Economy Youssef Boutros Ghali
has disclosed that the 6.7 per cent rate of growth of Egyptian
economy in 1998 will increase in 1999 to 6.9 per cent which is
three times the rate of population growth.
</P>
