average.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen has been ahead of all major Chinese cities for six
years in its exports, which were worth 26 billion U.S. dollars in
1998. They accounted for 14 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Output value of high-tech industries as a percentage of total
industrial output in Shenzhen was up to 38.7 last year, 3.7
percentage points higher than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in fixed assets amounted to 47.4 billion yuan last
year, 20 percent more than the previous year's.  
