<HEADLINE> German Trade Surplus Remains High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany posted a 10-year high in
their foreign trade surplus based on the totals for the last 11
months of 1998, the Federal Statistics Office in Wiesbaden said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In that period, the trade surplus was 129.7 billion marks
(76.3 billion U.S. dollars), which was close to the record high
of 134.5 billion marks (79.1 billion dollars) in 1989.
</P>
<P>
In addition, November saw a single-month record trade surplus
of 16.7 billion marks (9.8 billion dollars), the office said.
</P>
<P>
From January to November, the country's exports amounted to
871.4 billion marks (512.6 billion dollars), up 7.5 percent over
a year ago, while imports reached 741.7 billion marks (436.3
billion dollars), up five percent. 
