<HEADLINE> Doctors Working to Save Stabbing Victim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli doctors at Hadassah
Hospital are still trying to save the life of an old Palestinian
man, who was stabbed in East Jerusalem on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian man in his sixties is employed as a maintenance
worker at Israel's Magen David Adom Headquarters. He was stabbed
in the abdomen and neck.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police found a knife covered with blood near the scene
and the victim was found in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Transportation Shaul Yahalom issued a strong
statement condemning the attack, saying it was an unforgivable
act. He called upon security forces and police to do everything
possible to apprehend the attacker.
</P>
<P>
Stabbing incidents occurred in the city on several occasions in
the past, but the Israeli police had never found those responsible
for the attacks.
</P>
<P>
Last November, a Palestinian man called Mousa Al-Natsheh was
stabbed to death in East Jerusalem. 
</P>
