<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Business
Machines Corporation (IBM), the largest information technology
(IT) company in the world, has opened an IT education center here
to provide career training in computer software.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-Global Business System Limited would operate the IBM
Authorized Center for Education (IBM-ACE) in Bangladesh, The
Bangladesh Observer daily Tuesday quoted the visiting General
Manager of IBM Learning Service David Thomas as saying.
</P>
<P>
The IBM-ACE will provide IT education on the basis of seven
different curricula, which are framed considering the demand of IT
professionals in the international job market, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh could easily enter the global software export market
through building an IT workforce, another IBM official observed.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, IBM-ACE would provide career-oriented and
internationally recognized software education to Bangladeshi
students, the official added.
</P>
<P>
Later on, more branches of the IBM-ACE would be opened in
Bangladesh's major cities in phases, according to David Thomas.
