<HEADLINE> India Needs to Increase Contacts With EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Luxembourg Prime
Minister Jean-Claude Juncker said Tuesday that India needed to
increase its contacts with the European Union (EU) and his country
wanted to establish full-fledged ties with India.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen here, Juncker said that Luxembourg's
decision to open its embassy in New Delhi by next year would
facilitate contacts between the two countries. India has assured
that by then it would also open its embassy in Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day official visit, he held wide-ranging
discussions with Indian leaders on enhancing bilateral economic
relations. The two sides also exchanged instruments of
ratification of a bilateral agreement in the field of art,
culture, education, public health, mass media and sports. The
agreement was signed in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have recently concluded a bilateral air
services agreement and finalized a memorandum of understanding on
cooperation in the steel sector.
</P>
<P>
Juncker, who arrived here Sunday evening, said that his country
was in principle against the policy of protectionism and
anti-dumping measures as they would adversely affect the progress
of enhancing cooperation. 
</P>
