<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
Tuesday more than a quarter of a U.S. cent firmer, but off earlier
highs as the effects of profit taking and a stronger U.S. dollar
kicked in.
</P>
<P>
Strength in commodity prices, particularly gold, and the
Japanese yen against the U.S. dollar overnight and during the
morning session encouraged the local currency to one and a half
month highs.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished in Sydney at 63.77 U.S. cents
from Monday's close of 63.41 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
In offshore trade overnight the Australian dollar topped out at
64.12 U.S. cents and began the day around 64.00 U.S. cents. The
Australian dollar has not traded at these levels since November
25.
</P>
<P>
At the close of trading the Australian dollar was also buying
0.5552 Euro from 0.5473 while the Euro was buying 1.1488 U.S.
dollars, from 1.1583 U.S. dollars. 
