<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Greenspan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met
with Alan Greenspan, chairman of the Board of Governors of the US
Federal Reserve System, here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu briefed Greenspan on China's economic development in 1998.
He said that the spread of the Asian financial crisis, the
turmoil in the world financial market, and the unprecedented
flooding this summer have adversely affected China's economy.
</P>
<P>
China, however, has stimulated its economic growth by taking
active financial policies, a relevant currency policy of
maintaining the value of the Renminbi, and expanding the domestic
demand, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Greenspan expressed admiration over China's economic
achievements, and highly evaluated China's contribution to the
Asian and the world economy by keeping its currency exchange rate
stable.
</P>
<P>
He outlined the economic and financial development in the
U.S., and suggested that the two countries should reinforce their
co-operation in the financial sector. 
</P>
