<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dropped
5.13 points to 593.33, the all-share Emas index fell 1.59 points
to 151.05, the Industrial Index came down 7.86 points to 1,074.42
and the Second Board index lost 3.58 points to 169.32.
</P>
<P>
Losers overtook gainers by 589 to 109 while 91 counters were
unchanged, 124 counters untraded and 49 others suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover reduced to 200.140 million shares valued at
443.109 million ringgit (116.607 million U.S. dollars) compared to
303.846 million shares worth 641.301 million ringgit (168.763
million U.S. dollars) traded on Monday. 
</P>
