<HEADLINE> McKee Brothers Take 49ers Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- American brothers Jonathan
and Charlie McKee jumped from eighth to first place on the
leaderboard after Tuesday's races in the 49er world championships
in Melbourne, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The McKees had two wins and a second place on day three of the
series.
</P>
<P>
Defending world champion Chris Nicholson and his new crew Ed
Smyth trailed the McKees by three points.
</P>
<P>
They have the same score as fellow Australians John and Gary
Boyd but claim second place on countback.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Bruni brothers, Francesco and Gabrielle, also had a
good day with two firsts and a fourth. They lagged behind
Nicholson and Boyd by just one point.
</P>
<P>
With five more races to sail in this series, the championship
is still wide open. 
</P>
