<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Upcoming Four-Party Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China voiced the hope today
that the upcoming four-party talks this weekend in Geneva will
realize new achievements on the basis of what has already been
accomplished in both implementing the nuclear framework agreement
and promoting permanent peace in the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today
at a regular news briefing that the parties will take part in
substantial discussions this weekend on easing tension and
establishing a permanent peace mechanism for the region, as well
as on other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that China will continue to play a positive and
constructive role in dealing with these issues.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear framework agreement between the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea and the United States has been
earnestly implemented since it was signed, said Sun, who also
reiterated that China has always advocated the maintenance of
peace and stability in the peninsula, and has been doing
important work in this regard in its own way. 
</P>
