<HEADLINE> Ainslie on Course for Laser Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Ben Ainslie took
another step toward the Laser world title on Tuesday as he has a
14-point lead over Robert Scheidt of Brazil with two races left.
</P>
<P>
Ainslie won the first race of the day while Scheidt failed to
take a top three placing in either race nine or 10. The Briton
has won four races in the past three days while Scheidt has taken
just one.
</P>
<P>
He has looked every inch a winner here, sailing tactically
clever races and keeping a cool head throughout.
</P>
<P>
However, in this 12-heat series there is only one discardable
result. Ainslie already has that in his score and cannot afford a
slip-up against the very determined Brazilian.
</P>
<P>
The last day of this championship will be as much a battle of
minds as of sailing skills although Scheidt has to watch his
back, with third-placed Karl Suneson of Sweden only three points
behind. 
