<HEADLINE> World Food Program to Aid Lesotho Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program
(WFP) is to distribute food aid to early-childhood development
centers in Lesotho, Southern African Broadcasting Association
(SABA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
SABA quoted WFP officer for emergency operations, John Gerthy,
as saying that the exercise will start on January 20 to get food
to 186 centers in Maseru, capital of Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
Gerthy said the package comprises 50 tons of beans, cooking oil
and maize meal which would be enough food for the centers for
three months.
</P>
<P>
He said his organization is helping the childhood development
centers because most of them were destroyed during the unrest last
year.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 children between the age of two and five years
will benefit from the donation, said Gerthy.
</P>
<P>
SABA did not say when Gerthy made the remarks.
</P>
<P>
The WFP assistance is believed to be the first of its kind to
people affected by the destruction of businesses in the mountain
kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
