<HEADLINE> Twenty-three Teams To Attend Hongkong Rugby Sevens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three out of the 24
teams scheduled to participate in the Credit Suisse First Boston
Hong Kong Sevens have confirmed their participation, the Hong
Kong Rugby Football Union (HKRFU) said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The line-up for the 510,000 U.S. dollars tournament includes
traditional rugby powerhouses of New Zealand, Australia and South
Africa, Sevens specialists and defending champions Fiji, and
emerging rugby nations China and Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Scotland, Ireland and France have also confirmed their
attendance at the Sevens, giving the tournament strong
representation from the Home Unions and Five Nations.
</P>
<P>
After their inaugural appearance in 1998, the People's
Republic of China, together with other developing sides, will be h
oping to gain invaluable experience by competing against the top
teams in rugby, and seeking to emulate the entertaining attacking
style.
</P>
<P>
The HKRFU is still awaiting a response from another
international union to round out the final team.
</P>
<P>
The competition is to be held from March 26 to 28. 
</P>
