<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Banker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said this during a meeting with Frank G. Zarb, chairman and
chief executive officer of the National Association of Securities
Dealers, Inc. (NASD) of the Untied States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China's securities market is still in its
initial stage and there is much room for improvement.
</P>
<P>
He added that last year China was adversely affected by the
financial crisis in Asia and suffered from severe flooding.
However, China's national economy still enjoyed rapid development
as the Chinese government adhered to its reform policy and
adopted effective measures to tackle the problems.
</P>
