conducted by the Nasdaq Stock Market, Inc., which is affiliated
with the NASD. Nasdaq is the world's first completely electronic
stock market, existing without a trading hall. It has absorbed
many hi-tech companies onto its listed issues, and its
transaction volume is second in the world.
</P>
<P>
Zarb said that the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges have
advanced rapidly in recent years, and China has adopted the
correct policy by opening its capital market gradually and
discreetly.
</P>
<P>
He added that Nasdaq would like to cooperate with its Chinese
counterparts in advancing the technology of electronic stock
transactions and the supervision of capital markets. 
