<HEADLINE> Most People To Travel By Train During Spring Festival: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey indicates that
trains remains the first choice of Chinese people traveling
during Spring Festival (the Chinese Lunar New Year) which falls
on February 16 this year, according to a report in today's Economi
c Information Daily.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted among more than 600 residents of
Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Xi'an, Chengdu and Wuhan, shows
that 61 percent of the respondents plan to travel by train as a
safe and economical means of transportation.
</P>
<P>
Some 23 percent of those responding said they prefer to take
bus because of its flexibility and convenience, 12 percent said
they will travel by air for speed and comfort, and the remaining
4 percent will go by ship because of their geographical location.
</P>
<P>
In choosing long-distance transportation, nearly half said
safety is their first consideration, while 25 percent said price
is the deciding factor.
</P>
<P>
When asked which method of travel is most satisfying, some 40
percent of those questioned said planes, and 35 percent said they
still like the traditional train travel.
</P>
<P>
With regard to cost, some 60 percent of the respondents said
the price of air tickets should be lowered, 35 percent suggested
a computerized method of selling train tickets, while some 38 per
cent said buses should offer more comfort and better passenger
service.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
