<HEADLINE> Four Boats Destroyed, 12 Rebels killed in S. Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy's fast
attack craft engaged a fleet of Tamil rebel boats in Northern
Province Monday, destroying four of them and killing 12 rebels,
reports reaching here Tuesday said.
</P>
<P>
The attack began Monday night when Navy boats first detected
two rebel boats coming towards the Naval vessels, a Navy spokesman
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
One rebel boat caught fire while the other fled. Then the Navy
detected four more rebel boats coming towards them, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Three of them were destroyed and the other limped back to the
sea.
</P>
<P>
The fighting continued till early Tuesday morning. The Tamil
rebels may have been transporting some of their area leaders to a
point off Kuchchaveli region, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan gun boats last week destroyed a flotilla of rebel
boats, killing at least 25 rebels.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Navy has strengthened patrol around
Kuchchaveli, as the Tamil rebels, who are fighting for a separate
state in the north and east of the country, have sent
reinforcements to the area in the last two weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
