<HEADLINE> Smigun Awards Estonia First-ever World Cup Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Kristina Smigun awarded Estonia
its first-ever World Cup victory in cross country skiing by
taking the women's 15-kilometer freestyle race in Nove Mesto, the
Czech Republic on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Smigun, who had her previous best runner-up position in a
sprint last month, crossed the finish line in 42 minutes 41.5
seconds, beating Italy's Stefania Belmondo by 16.1 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Nina Gavriljuk finished third in 43:04.3, edging her
teammates Anfisa Reztsova in a season-best fourth and Svetlana
Nagejkina in fifth.
</P>
<P>
Posting a brilliant run, Smigun got into the lead in the
second half of the race, and, despite being closely trailed by
Belmondo until the 13th kilometer, managed to step up her pace
and win.
</P>
<P>
Belmondo, a specialist in freestyle skiing, has yet to win a
World Cup race this season.
</P>
<P>
Overall World Cup leader Bente Martinsen, who won Saturday's
10-kilometer classic, finished a disappointing 14th while
Katerina Neumannova of the Czech Republic, second in the overall
world Cup standings, came home 12th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
