Democratic Party (PDP) has reaffirmed superiority by winning the
governorship in 20 states, out of a total of 35, where elections
were held.
</P>
<P>
The All People's Party (APP) came second with nine governorship
seats, while the Alliance for Democracy (AD) bagged six, all in
the southwest.
</P>
<P>
The PDP also captured 443 seats in the state House of Assembly
elections and led in 17 states, according to results released so
far by the Independent National Electoral Commission.
</P>
<P>
The APP and AD won 238 and 163 seats respectively. 
