<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Losses on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended losses
on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday in line with the weaker
sentiment across the region following Wall Street's overnight
loss.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was spooked by a Brazilian state debt
moratorium.
</P>
<P>
They said overvaluations of most stocks and talk that domestic
interest rates have neared the bottom also contributed to the
fall.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 6.10 points to
close at 1,536.98 points, bouncing back from the intraday low of
1507.55 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume surged up to 606.87 million units worth 650.70
million Singapore dollars (387.60 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outstripped losers by 263 to 59 with 97 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 45.15 million stocks parcel by CK Tang
w99 that topped the actives chart of the day. CK Tang was the
second most heavily traded share with a turnover of 40.99 million
units. ERL was next with 30.54 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the biggest gainer of the day as it ran up by 50
cents to finish at 6.70 Singapore dollars. It was followed by C &AMP;
C that climbed up 30 cents to close at 6.70 Singapore dollars.
Cerebos picked up 27cents to end at 2.92 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 remained the biggest loser of the
day dropping by 90 cents to 26.60 Singapore dollars. UOB F was
next retreating 70 cents to 10.90 Singapore dollars. OCBC F sank
40 cents to end at 12.70 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
