<HEADLINE> Laid-Off Henan Workers Find New Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 460,000 people declared
redundant by state-owned enterprises in central China's Henan
Province found new jobs in 1998 as a result of local efforts to
expand re-employment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
