<HEADLINE> China Increasing Intellectual Property Rights Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China plans to increase
efforts to protect intellectual property rights to meet the
challenges of the new information-based economy, according to
Jiang Ying, the director of the State Intellectual Property
Office.
</P>
<P>
Jiang says that protecting intellectual property rights means
protecting the market, which will allow the healthy development
of the information-based economy.
</P>
<P>
Jiang says that his office will adopt various measures that
better protect intellectual property rights by setting up
intellectual property rights departments nationwide, increasing
legislation, cracking down on those who infringe on intellectual
property rights, and cooperating internationally in protecting
intellectual property rights. 
</P>
