<HEADLINE> Pakistan President Confers Award on Chinese Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Rafique
Tarar Tuesday conferred the award of "Hilar-i-Pakistan" (Crescent
Pakistan) on outgoing Chinese Ambassador Zhang Chengli in
recognition of his dedication to further strengthening the
Pakistan-China friendship.
</P>
<P>
In a brief but impressive ceremony in the Presidential House,
Tarar awarded the highest honor for civil officials in the country
to the Chinese envoy for his four-year "meritorious services and
his dedication to further strengthening and expanding the
Pakistan-China relations."
</P>
<P>
Zhang "displayed the highest standards of diplomatic conduct,
acumen and professional skill which has contributed greatly to the
promotion of Pakistan-China relations," remarked a senior official
from the Cabinet Secretariat, who presided over the ceremony
attended by dozens of diplomats and government officials.
</P>
<P>
In a brief meeting shortly before the awarding ceremony, the
president expressed his appreciation for the Chinese ambassador's
personal contribution during his tenure to the long-standing
friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is Pakistan's most trusted friend and
Pakistan will never forget China's generous assistance and support
to Pakistan during difficult times.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Zhang said that it is not only a great honor for him
to be awarded "Hilar-i-Pakistan" but also a great honor for the
Chinese government and the Chinese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
