<HEADLINE> Murdoch Agrees with Blatter's Biennial World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Media tycoon Rupert Murdoch
praised FIFA president Sepp Blatter's proposal to have a World
Cup every two years at a forum on media in the 21st century here
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"My first reaction to that is it's a very good idea," Mudoch
said, "Certainly soccer is so strong and so popular in so many
parts of the world that we should see major international
competition more than every four years. I would agree with that."
</P>
<P>
Blatter put forward his idea of turning the quadrennial World
Cup to a biennial one this month, and it caused worldwide
controversy.
</P>
<P>
UEFA officials feared that the every-two-year tournament would
pose a threat to the European Championship.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's Strategic Studies Committee, which can propose changes t
o international competitions, will discuss Blatter's suggestion
this month. 
</P>
