<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Second Tranche of Loan to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Tuesday approved the release of 500 million U.S. dollars of the
Financial Governance Reform Loan for Indonesia, the second tranche
of a 1.4-billion-dollar policy loan approved by the bank in June
1998.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement issued here, the Manila-based bank said
the Indonesian government has completed a large number of policy
reforms in areas of financial sector restructuring, improved
governance practices in public and private sectors and increased
disclosure and transparency of financial information.
</P>
<P>
"These will contribute to continued progress in achieving
macro-economic stability under the most difficult circumstances,"
the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The 1.4-billion-dollar policy loan, which supports the
country's financial governance reform program aimed at addressing
the weakness in the financial and public sector, was set to be
disbursed in three tranches. The first tranche of 500 million
dollars was released shortly after the approval of the loan last
June.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank has also approved a 2.47-million-dollar
technical assistance grant to help Indonesia undertake
comprehensive reforms of state-owned enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
