<DOCNO> XIE19990112.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 27 Swans Die from Poisoning and Illegal Hunting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of white swans which
flew to Sanmenxia on the Yellow River in central China's Henan
Province earlier this month have seen 27 of their companions die
either from poisoning or illegal hunting.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen others have had narrow escapes from death after being
treated by local veterinarians, according to the China
Environmental News.
</P>
<P>
The police in Shaanxian County of the city of Sanmenxia
stopped a 40-year-old local farmer, Zhao Shishi, as he was
cycling down a road near the spot where the swans were found
dead, and discovered a bag on Zhao's motorcycle filled with
poisoned water birds belonging to another species under county
protection.
</P>
<P>
The police searched the suspect's home, where they found nine
other dead water birds and more than 10 kilograms of poison. Zhao
pleaded guilty in the face of this solid evidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
