<HEADLINE> 12 Philippine Players Suffer Food Poisoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Twelve Philippine national
players of the Special Olympics for the disabled suffered food
poisoning in Baguio, the Northern Philippines, Monday night and
were rushed to hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency Tuesday quoted hospital sources as
saying that all the 12 victims are now recuperating and "are
already out of danger".
</P>
<P>
Based on initial investigation, the agency said, the 12
victims started vomiting just after eating Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The victims are among more than 500 athletes and officials
billeted at the Teachers Camp in Baguio for the annual sports
event for the disabled, it said.
</P>
<P>
The players of the special sports events were the blind and
other kinds of disabled persons, the agency said. 
