<HEADLINE> UAE to Hold International Security Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition
featuring the most advanced technology in commercial security and
safety will be held in the United Arab Emirates' (UAE) port city
of Dubai on February 8-10.
</P>
<P>
InterSec '99, the first of its kind to be held in Dubai since
1995, will allow businesses and government organizations to view
the latest security products for protection of assets and people,
and in the management of fire and other risks.
</P>
<P>
Products and services on display will include closed circuit
television and surveillance systems, access control, alarm
systems, safes, sprinkler systems, fire detectors, fire-fighting
equipment and vehicles, safety clothing and personnel protection
equipment, breathing apparatus, anti-terrorism services and
equipment and safety training courses.
</P>
<P>
Justin Boutros, Managing Director of Channels LLC, which
organizes the exhibition, said the initiative to hold the
exhibition is based on strong growth in the security and safety
sector across the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
Market research confirms the demand for safety and
security products and services is stronger than ever in the Gulf
region.
</P>
<P>
At least 60 safety and security specialists from the UAE and
major companies from the U.S., Canada, France, Finland, Germany,
Italy and Britain will attend the exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
