<HEADLINE> 7 Egyptian Soccer Fans Killed, 14 Injured in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Eight Egyptian soccer fans have
been killed and 14 others injured in a stampede at Alexandria
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy took place at 19:15 local time (1715 GMT) Monday,
one hour before a football match between the clubs of Itihard and
Karroum, according to Egypt's Al Ahram daily published on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Soccer fans rushed to the front-row seats of the third stand,
only finding that they were obstructed by locked doors to the
seats.
</P>
<P>
The fans in the front were pushed to fall onto the ground and
trampled.
</P>
<P>
The injured were immediately rushed to hospitals and eight of
them died on the road. 
