<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China National Petroleum Pushing Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The China National Petroleum
Corporation (CNPC) plans to spend 10.4 billion yuan on oil and
gas exploration in the new year.
</P>
<P>
The state company says it will continue to pay close attention
to oil and gas exploration in western China and using more
advanced technology. It expects to get better results from
exploration and to consider markets both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
It reports that it is likely to add 360.5 million tons of
proven oil reserves and 94 billion cubic meters of proven gas
reserves, mainly in western China this year.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, CNPC found five large oil and gas areas in western
and southwestern China and three 100-million-ton oilfields in the
Tarim, Junggar and Ordos basins. It also located oil and gas reser
ves in ten 100-million-ton oilfields that it found in 1997 and
added 485 million ton of proven oil reserves and 223.2 billion
cubic meters of proven natural gas reserves. 
</P>
