<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Shut Down Foot-Washing Bars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The city of Guangzhou in south
China will shut down all of the foot-washing and hand-washing
bars.
</P>
<P>
The city will also remove all advertising signs with the words
"massage", "foot-washing" and "hands-washing," said today's
Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
The capital of Guangdong Province has more than 500 businesses
involved in massage and foot-washing, of which a considerable
number have no licenses and even offer prostitution.
</P>
<P>
All businesses offering massages not done by blind people
should close at once, said a municipal government official.
</P>
<P>
The city has also banned barbers for massaging body parts
other than the head. "All the massage beds in barbers shops will
be confiscated," the official added.
</P>
<P>
The city also stressed that massage parlors should perform
only those functions in line with their licenses.  
</P>
