<HEADLINE> Patent Services Free for Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Patent Office has
pledged to provide free services for all laid-off workers in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The office recently opened a phone hot-line for services
including patent applications, evaluation, and transfer and
protection, the first of its kind in the nation.
</P>
<P>
Callers will be able to gain detailed information on 210,000
expired patents which are no longer protected, according to a
Beijing Economic Daily report.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city's laid-off workers are entitled to apply
for patents at reduced fees or free of charge.
</P>
<P>
The hot-line has been in trial operation for nearly two
months, and ten to twenty people call in every day, officials
were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Even some residents of Taiwan and Macao have called in to
inquire about these services, and senior patent experts and
experienced professors are manning the line to answer questions
from callers, the report said.  
</P>
