<HEADLINE> U.S. and British Embassies in Uganda Close for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Embassy and the
British High Commission in Uganda has been closed following
threats by an anonymous caller that a bomb was to be planted in
the premises.
</P>
<P>
An official in the U.S. embassy, who declined to be named, told
Xinhua in a telephone interview Tuesday morning that the embassy
is closed and that he does not know when it will reopen.
</P>
<P>
The staff in both embassies were told not to report for duty
until further notice, the New Vision reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted an official in the U.S. embassy as saying
Monday that the embassy will not open until the security
normalizes.
</P>
<P>
U.S. and British missions were closed on December 17 in fear of
 retaliatory strikes after their countries bombed targets in Iraq.
 Similar anonymous callers have rung the two missions in the past
leading to their temporary closure.
</P>
<P>
Since Nairobi and Dar-es-Salaam bombings last August, the two
embassies have received numerous bombing threats. Other agencies
of the two countries in Kampala have also been targets of threats.
 
</P>
