BEIJING, January 12 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to make
great effort on the development of its biological engineering
pharmaceutical sector to help transform it into one of the
country's pillar industries within 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Sources from a national conference on research and development
of new pharmaceuticals, which was held here Monday, revealed
there are plans to increase the annual output value of the
bio-engineering pharmaceutical industry to at least 100 billion
yuan (about 12 billion U.S. dollars) in the 15 years.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 3,300 enterprises in China involved in
manufacturing bio-engineering pharmaceuticals, producing
approximately 3,400 kinds of pharmaceuticals in 47 categories.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the bio-engineering industry witnessed an annual
growth rate of over 20 percent and its annual output value
reached 12.5 billion yuan (1.5 million U.S. dollars) with export
value up to 550 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The conference discussed the country's 15-year development
program for the industry and revealed that China will focus on
research of biological materials, working human biological
projects and the application of information technology in the
medical field.
</P>
<P>
The country will also establish a biological engineering
research center and support the building of industrial bases for
manufacturing pharmaceuticals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
