<HEADLINE> ADB to Help Pension System Reform in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
announced here Tuesday that it has approved a 2.4 million U.S.
dollar technical assistance grant to help China undertake a
comprehensive reform of its pension system.
</P>
<P>
"This is considered essential to the country's successful
transition to a socialist market economy," the bank said in a
statement issued here.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that the technical assistance will support the
formulation and implementation of the administrative, legal,
regulatory and supervisory frameworks for the new pension system.
</P>
<P>
It will also help facilitate the development of financial and
insurance markets, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The technical assistance program will be implemented over a
period of one year, starting in March 1999, it said. 
</P>
