<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hottest Year in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- 1998 was New Zealand's
hottest since records began last century.
</P>
<P>
According to the national climate summary issued Tuesday by the
 National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research, the
country's average temperature last year was 13.4 degrees Celsius,
0.8 degrees Celsius above average.
</P>
<P>
Since records began in 1853, the previous highest figures in
New Zealand were 13.3 degrees Celsius in 1971 and 13.2 degrees
Celsius in 1989 and 1990.
</P>
<P>
1998 was described as "one of the most dramatic" in New
Zealand's climatic history, with records of extreme temperature
and high rainfall, as well as severe drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
