<HEADLINE> Ajax Cape Town to Be Born in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 12 (Xinhua) -- African Ajax will be
formed from a merger of two local teams in Cape Town, South
Africa in June.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed on Monday, Dutch soccer giant Ajax
Amsterdam will franchise its name out to the new team.
</P>
<P>
The 4.4 million U.S. dollars deal regulated that Ajax will own
51 percent of Ajax Cape Town and can choose top players to play
in the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The new club will benefit from first-class training and
European expertise.
</P>
<P>
"For the first time in the history of professional football
and, indeed, professional sports, a major club is franchising
itself into another major market," said Ajax chairman Michael van
Praag. 
</P>
