<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, SAARC to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
offer further cooperation in diverse ways with the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) and cement ties
between the two regional groups, diplomats here said.
</P>
<P>
The economic cooperation will focus on investment through the
European Community Investment Partners Scheme, under which the EU
will publish an Asia-Invest report on Sri Lanka this year, German
Ambassador Helmut Van Edig told a press conference Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Ambassador of the EU Iuka Uusitalo told the joint press
conference that Sri Lanka would have an important role to play in
furthering cooperation between the regional groups as Sri Lanka is
both chairing the SAARC and has one of its diplomats as secretary
general of the organization.
</P>
<P>
Uusitalo said the EU with its experience of integration would
be able to provide training to the SAARC Secretariat to strength
itself.
</P>
<P>
In terms of direct cooperation between the two blocks, SAARC
could apply for the Generalized System of Preference, said
Uusitalo, adding that under such a scheme, goods from the region
produced with its own resources would get preferential status,
which would also facilitate trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
