<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAS to Set up Anti-Drug Policy Evaluation Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
American States (OAS) will launch this year a mechanism to
evaluate the anti-drug policy of its member countries, OAS
Secretary-General Cesar Gaviria said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gaviria told the press that the OAS mechanism is designed to
counter the annual United States anti-narcotics certification
process.
</P>
<P>
The OAS mechanism will be supported by every country,
including the United States, and will create a climate of
cooperation and not confrontation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
It "will be a very important element of anti-drug policy " in
the continent, Gaviria said after his arrival here for a regional
meeting on antipersonnel mines.
</P>
<P>
Gaviria, former Colombian president, added that the OAS made
the decision on the mechanism following one year of research by
the Interamerican Anti-Drug Cooperation Center, made up of
regional anti-narcotics agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
