<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cold Wave Kills 11 in Northern Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 people died in the
cold wave that has been sweeping Bangladesh's north and
northwestern region since Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Monday's temperature in the Rangpur district was nine degrees
Celsius, while the lowest temperature fell to 6.5 degrees Celsius
at Ishurdi district on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The temperature elsewhere over the northern part of the country
ranged from 7 to 9 degrees Celsius, according to the Met Office.
</P>
<P>
Besides, most of the districts in the region were even with out
the sun for several days, said press reports reaching here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Normal life was paralyzed due to the severe cold in the region,
which has caused immense sufferings to the poor people.
</P>
<P>
The local district governments are distributing blankets and
warm clothes among the distressed.
</P>
<P>
The sudden fall in the night temperature was caused by the
movement of the subcontinent high that was persisting over the
Madhya Pradesh, Bihar and adjoining West Bangla and on the land
areas comprising Bangladesh, weather experts observed.
</P>
<P>
The cold wave would continue for three or four days, a senior
meteorologist said, adding after that temperature "may rise
gradually before the bite of winter later this month or early next
month." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
