<DOCNO> XIE19990112.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian PM Repeats Appeal for Unity of Ethnic Albanians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli
Majko renewed the appeal Monday to ethnic Albanians in Serbia's
Kosovo province for speaking with one voice in settling the
Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government supports only a political solution
that favors the respect for the will of the Albanian people in
Kosovo as well as for international principles and rules, Majko
said in a meeting with Bujar Bukoshi, prime minister of the
self-claimed ethnic Albanian government in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Such a solution should be one acceptable not only to any
individual person or political force but also to all parties
concerned, Majko said.
</P>
<P>
Bukoshi backed Majko's initiatives, saying that all the
political organizations should reach understanding through talks
and formulate a common program.
</P>
<P>
Bukoshi said his "government" will be composed of
representatives of all ethnic Albanian political forces.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanians, the majority of the population of
Kosovo, have long sought independence from Serbia and broken
into many bloody conflicts with Serbians. However, these
Albanians have power struggle among themselves.
</P>
<P>
The invitation of Bukoshi to visit Tirana is part of Majko's
efforts to unify the various political forces of Kosovo's ethnic
Albanians, according to Musa Ulqini, Albania's minister of
information.
</P>
<P>
Prior to Bukoshi's visit, Kosovo Albanian Democratic Movement
Chairman Rexhep Qosja and Adem Demaci, political representative
of the Kosovo Liberation Army, visited Albania on January 8 and
4, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
