<DOCNO> XIE19990112.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, Interpol Investigate Billionaire's Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police and the
Interpol are investigating how a Tamil billionaire businessman had
sent out of the country about 12 billion rupees (200 million U.S.
dollars) illegally in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said Tuesday that the 36-year-old businessman,
considered to be a close friend of Tamil rebel leader Velupillai
Prabhakaran, had been arrested by the Criminal Investigation
Department (CID) recently.
</P>
<P>
The CID and the Interpol have found that the suspect had
credited the illegally remitted funds to accounts of certain
individuals and organizations in more than 950 banks all over the
world.
</P>
<P>
The CID also found that the businessman and the Tamil rebel
leader had been neighbors at Velvetithurai in northern Sri Lanka
and close friends during their youth.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the businessman had acquired his wealth only a
few years ago. They suspect his money had been used to purchase
arms for the rebel movement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
