<HEADLINE> Internet to Reach Half UK Adults This Year: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half of the adults in the
UK will be wired up to the Internet by the end of this year,
according to an opinion poll published Monday in the Guardian
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Though under one-third of adults in Britain, 29 percent, are
now online, the survey showed that Internet growth in Britain
looks set to surge with a further 14 percent saying they plan to
get connected within the next 12 months.
</P>
<P>
That means the figure of people hooked up to the Internet is
expected to rise to 43 percent, nearly half of the adult
population, by the millennium, the Guardian reported.
</P>
<P>
This also indicates a rate of expansion more than double than
twice that of last year's 1 percent a month, according to the
poll.
</P>
<P>
The growth confirms that the Internet has caught on faster than
any previous new technology, including video recorders and CDs.
</P>
<P>
It shows that the Internet is lifting off in Britain as a mass
medium widely used by the public and is no longer the specialist
preserve of academics, scientists and "net nerds," the newspaper
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
