<HEADLINE> France Hopes Strong Relations with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The French foreign minister arrived in Moscow on an official
visit on Monday afternoon, the Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Izvestia newspaper, Vedrine said that
making preparations for the coming visit to Paris by the Russian
President Boris Yeltsin is one of the aims of his visit.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin will visit France late this month, Vedrine said,
noting that personal contacts between the French and Russian
presidents continue to play an important role in the development
of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Asked to what extent French diplomacy will pay attention to
the nationalist and anti-Western sentiments which were displayed
in Russia recently, the French foreign minister said there is no
need to pay much attention to these moods.
</P>
<P>
"There is nothing surprising that some want to use the suff
erings or apprehensions of people for political ends, but
constant vigilance and wise replies are needed in this case," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Vedrine hailed the fact that the Russian supreme
authorities confirmed their loyalty to reforms and continued the
dialogue with their Western partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
