<HEADLINE> EDS- Russia Academy of Sciences Will Mark 275th Anniversary in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Russia has prepared a program
of jubilee events to be celebrated in the capital during the year
1999. The programs will be devoted to the 275th anniversary of
the Russian Academy of Sciences (RAS), the Itar-Tass news agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The jubilee events program was designed by the RAS and the
Ministry of Science and Technology. The events include a one-day
enlarged session of the RAS presidium, which will be held in
St.Petersburg, while the main celebrations will be conducted at
the State Kremlin Palace in June 1999.
</P>
<P>
Measures to support Russian science and scientists have also
been worked out. The country plans to build new and better
housing for young scientists who are working in scientific
centers in the Far East, Siberia, the Urals and Central Russia,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The academy and ministry are also considering restoring the
great museum of anthropology and ethnology, the St.Petersburg hot
house complex at the Botanical Institute, and the complex of bu
ildings "Neskuchny Sad" at the Russian Academy of Sciences.
</P>
</TEXT>
