<HEADLINE> Russia to Set Up Space Rocket Complex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny
Primakov decreed on Monday that the government set up a space
rocket complex of the Strela type at Svobodny cosmodrome, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The rocket complex at Svobodny cosmodrome is part of the
Russian federal space program and will be financed from
extrabudget funds, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
From now on, the Moscow Institute of Heat Engineering and
state enterprises will participate in financing the maintenance
of Svobodny cosmodrome on the basis of agreements with the
Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry, the Russian Space Agency, and a number
of enterprises will define procedures regarding participation in
the maintenance of facilities and infrastructure of the co
smodrome to ensure the operation of Start and Strela space rocket
complexes. 
</P>
