<HEADLINE> Intel to Introduce New Generation of Microprocessor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The chip giant Intel Corp.
is expected to announce Monday that it has developed its next
generation microprocessor Pentium III, that can be used to turn
computers into digital-video recorders, apart from other
functions.
</P>
<P>
According to the Wall Street Journal, Intel will ship the first
versions of Pentium III, with speeds of 450MHZ to 500MHZ, in
February or March this year.
</P>
<P>
Pentium III's raw speed is close to the top Pentium II chips
now available, but the new one will be better at multimedia
processing because it includes 70 new instructions that are
specifically aimed at speeding up graphics, communications, audio
and video process.  
</P>
