<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Carbon Monoxide Poisoning Kills Two in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Carbon monoxide trapped by
an ice-clogged chimney killed a couple and sickened 17 others
including their daughter and neighbors in three adjoining
buildings in Delaware State in Eastern U.S. Sunday, said reports
reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fire-fighters initially responded to reports of a gas leak at an
apartment building in Wilmington on Sunday, the reports quoted
fire battalion chief Al Huelsenbeck as saying.
</P>
<P>
They soon discovered the gas was emanating from next door, and
when rescue workers forced their way into the house, they found
two people dead, Huelsenbeck said. The carbon monoxide level
inside the house was more than 10 times the level at which carbon
monoxide detectors are set to ring, he said.
</P>
<P>
In all, 17 people required medical treatment, including 11 at
the apartment building next to the house where the deaths
occurred, and people in two other adjoining buildings.
</P>
<P>
Investigators found that the chimney and furnace flue were
clogged with dirt, soot, broken bricks, birds' nests, leaves and
ice. The cold weather probably froze all the material solid,
sealing up the small holes so none of the exhaust could get out,
the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990112.0314 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Meets Chinese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa met with visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan at the State House her Monday to discuss ways to
strengthen bilateral cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his pleasant visit to China last April, Mkapa told
Tang that it's his responsibility to further develop, together
with his Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin, the cordial relation
cultivated by Mao Zedong and Julius Nyerere in the early 1960s.
</P>
<P>
"We'll realize their foresighted expectations on the bilateral
relations by deepening bilateral political cooperation and
consultations and boosting various forms of cooperation by the
enterprises of both sides," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa reiterated in his one-hour meeting that Tanzania is
consistent in upholding the principled stand of "one China", and
that such a stand will never see any change.
</P>
<P>
Tang said history has proved that China and Tanzania are the
all- weather sincere friends of mutual trust since the two
countries forged diplomatic ties more than 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Tanzanian friendship reared by both leaders of the old
 generation has also found new forms in the fields of economic and
trade cooperation to keep abreast of the times, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the reform of the Sino-Tanzanian Friendship Textile
Company from the state-to-state ownership to the joint venture by
both enterprises is one of the gratifying achievements in the wake
of the well-known 1,860- km Tanzania-Zambia Railway.
</P>
<P>
"China will encourage more of its powerful and prestigious
enterprises and companies to invest in Tanzania to try to
contribute to its economic development," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the relations between China and African countries, Tang
noted that China's foreign policy remain based upon strengthening
its cooperation with the vast developing countries including those
in Africa.
</P>
<P>
"In line with its African brothers, China will work for
maintaining the just rights and interests of the developing
countries in a bid to establish a just and reasonable new
international order for politics and economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who is on his fourth leg of an African tour which has
brought him to Egypt, Kenya and Uganda, is expected to visit some
Sino-Tanzanian joint ventures Tuesday before departing for his
last stop in Zambia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
