<HEADLINE> Mozambique Concerned over Illegal Immigrants in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Minister of Interior
Almerino Manhenje has said that the government is concerned over
the situation of Mozambique's illegal immigrants in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government insists on dialog with the South
Africa to coordinate their stands on issues of refugee
repatriation, the Noticias newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We are working with the South African authorities to ensure
Mozambicans' deserved treatment in South Africa," said Manhenje.
</P>
<P>
 The report said every week a large number of illegal
Mozambican immigrants are repatriated by the South African
authorities through Ressano Garcia border post. The Mozambicans
were reportedly packed in overloaded train and were mal-treated.
</P>
<P>
Some repatriatees said illegal Mozambican immigrants were
treated as slaves by South African farmers who reported to local
police at the end of the month before pay day so that the
immigrants were deprived of their salaries or even arrested and
repatriated.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, it is unfair for South African
farmers and police to treat Mozambicans in that manner. He
stressed that Mozambican authorities will hold dialog to settle
the issue.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
