<HEADLINE> urgent :  ECOMOG Troops Recapture State House in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The west African peacekeeping
force ECOMOG has successfully taken control of the State House in
the Sierra Leonean capital Freetown, a statement said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the headquarters of the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS) in the Nigerian capital
Abuja said that its peacekeeping troops had driven rebels from the
State House near the center of Freetown.
</P>
<P>
The rebels are now being pushed out of Freetown following
ECOMOG'S reinforcement during the past few days, it said, adding
that "efforts are being made to flush the rebels out of private
residences in Freetown where some of them are still taking
refuge."
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, ECOWAS Secretary-General Lansana
Kouyate will travel to Lome, Togo, on Tuesday to meet Togolese
President Gnassingbe Eyadema, current ECOWAS chairman, for
emergency talks on the situation in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
It noted, "Consultations are currently going on between ECOWAS
heads of state and parties to the conflict with a view to
convening a meeting on the crisis as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
During the past two days, several hundreds of Nigerian soldiers
have been sent to Sierra Leone to reinforce the 15,000-strong
ECOMOG troops which have been battling for the control of the
capital city Freetwon with the rebels since last Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
