<HEADLINE> Five Zimbabweans Killed in Congo (K) Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Five Zimbabwean men deployed on
a military mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) were
killed after their aircraft crash-landed a few kilometers outside
the capital Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Zimbabwean Defense Forces (ZDF) Monday
said the Casa 212 crashed as a result of a combination of
technical problems and poor weather.
</P>
<P>
The death of the five men brings to 31 the number of reported
deaths of Zimbabweans taking part in the DRC war that erupted on
August 2 last year.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe, along with Namibia and Angola are fighting the
Congolese rebels who are trying to topple the government of
President Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
The date of the crash was not given and the ZDF said the names
of the deceased would be released once their next of kin had been
advised.
</P>
<P>
A summit seeking to secure a peace agreement between the rebels
and Kabila is scheduled for Lusaka, Zambia this week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
