<HEADLINE> Annan: Iraqi Parliament's Vote to Pose Challenge to UN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 11 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan said on Monday that the vote by the Iraqi parliament
would pose a major challenge to the United Nations Security
Council and the U.N.
</P>
<P>
Annan made the statement upon arriving at the headquarters of
the United Nations Headquarters this morning.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's parliament on Sunday passed a resolution,, calling for
further discussions on all U.N. resolutions on Iraq declared after
the 1991 Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
"I think this will pose a major challenge for the Security
Council and the U.N.," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
"There are lots of noises coming out of Iraq and I think we
need to wait awhile to assess what is actually happening including
the threats against Kuwait and Saudi Arabia," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
