<HEADLINE> UK Trying to Restore Relations With Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 11 (Xinhua) - The United Kingdom is trying to
restore its diplomatic relations with Sudan, which was destroyed
last year after the United States bombed a factory near Sudan's
capital Khartoum, a Foreign Office minister said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We have been in contact with the Sudanese to see if we can
remedy the situation," Baroness Liz Symons said in a written
answer to a parliamentary question.
</P>
<P>
Britain withdrew its diplomats from Khartoum last August after
the Sudanese government recalled its ambassador to London in
protest at British support for the U.S. bombing of the El Shifa
factory in Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
U.S. said the factory was "terrorist-related", but Sudan
maintained insisted that it was a harmless pharmaceutical plant.
</P>
<P>
A Foreign Office spokeswoman said Britain had always regretted
the need to close its embassy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
