<HEADLINE> Angola Lowers Age Limit for Recruits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Angola's Defense Ministry
announced Monday that recruit registration started from January 8
to February 16 for all citizens between 18 and 20 years of age,
lowering the previous legitimate age for recruits by two years.
</P>
<P>
The ministry warned that anyone who does not register on time
will be deemed as committing a crime and be punished by the law.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said the lowering of age limit by the Angolan
government is a result of the spreading of internal armed
conflicts which caused shortage of soldiers on the part of the
government army in the face of a series of new attacks across the
country by the opposition National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The two sides confronted in intense clashes both in central and
 northern Angola since last November.
</P>
<P>
A military source revealed that the younger and inexperienced
recruits will not be sent to the forefront to fight UNITA forces,
but instead be stationed in newly-recovered cities for security.
</P>
</TEXT>
