<HEADLINE> Cyprus Popular Bank Group Buys Insurance Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Popular Bank Group, one of the
major banking institutions in Cyprus, announced on Monday its 47
million Cyprus pounds (94 million U.S. dollars) take-over bid for
three insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
The bid covers the Paneuropean Insurance Co. Ltd. and its two
affiliates, Interamerican and Philiki, currently controlled by the
Shacolas Group of Companies.
</P>
<P>
The Shacolas Group has agreed to the bid.
</P>
<P>
Kikis Lazarides, Popular Bank Group Executive Chairman, told a
press conference that the Popular Bank will pay 1.55 pounds (3.10
dollars) per share and 55 cents (1.10 dollar) per warrant for the
Paneuropean company.
</P>
<P>
For the Interamerican and Philiki, the price agreed is 1.30
pounds (2.60 dollars) per share and 30 cents (0.60 dollars) per
warrant, he added.
</P>
<P>
After the take-over, the Popular Bank Group's market share will
reach 30 percent, securing a leading role in both life and general
insurance in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition will also allow the group to expand its
insurance activities in both Greece and Britain.
</P>
<P>
In response to the take-over, price index at the Cyprus Stock
Exchange on Monday went up 3.7 percent while index of the
insurance sector rose by a record 14.37 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
