<HEADLINE> Russian Commander on Efficiency of Strikes on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian Air Force Commander
Anatoly Kornukov said Monday that the efficiency of the American
and British strikes on Iraq in the Desert Fox operation was only
50 percent efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency quoted Kornukov as saying tha:"the
Russian Defense Ministry closely followed the developments in Iraq
and analyzed all possible consequences."
</P>
<P>
"In our preliminary estimate, the efficiency of the strikes
stood at 50 percent," he said, adding that some of the strikes
were inaccurate.
</P>
<P>
The commander announced that interest in Russian defense
systems had increased after the Desert Fox operation.
</P>
<P>
"Our reconnaissance and missile complexes are not inferior to
foreign ones. The S-300 missile is no worse than the American
Patriot," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that research centers are now working on the creation
of a single command structure for the Russian strategic deterrence
forces.
</P>
<P>
Kornukov noted that Russian President Boris Yeltsin, the
commander-in-chief of the Russian armed forces, is to have the
final say on this matter.
</P>
<P>
The single strategic deterrence forces command structure is
expected to control all services possessing nuclear weapons: the
strategic rocket forces, strategic nuclear naval fleet and
strategic air forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
