<HEADLINE> Lesotho's Mutinous Soldiers put on Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mothae was speaking ahead of the start of the mutiny trial in
Maseru.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho radio said earlier that 50 army officers were standing
trial on charges of mutiny following the dismissal of the military
commander and other 27 senior officers last September.
</P>
<P>
The mutinous soldiers removed Lieutenant-General Makhula
Mosakeng and 27 other officers by force during their rebellion,
which was defused by Botswanan and South African intervention
troops.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said that the mutinous soldier may be sentenced
to death if they are found guilty.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers rebelled against the government of Prime Minister
Pakalitha Mosisili after weeks of opposition objecting to the
outcome of the general elections in last May.
</P>
<P>
Human rights and opposition groups in Lesotho condemned the
court martial as an abuse of the constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
