<HEADLINE> Trading Volume Drops at Nairobi Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, JANUARY 11 (Xinhua) -- Trading activity was slackened
at Nairobi Stock Exchange (NSE) Monday as turnover fell by more
than 50 percent to stand at 11.7 million Shillings (some 60
Shillings equal to one U.S. Dollars) at close of business,
according to an available source here.
</P>
<P>
However, the 20-share index at NSE extended its month-long
rally into another week increasing by 0.12 percent to stand at
3123.87 percent. The index last week crossed the 3,000-point
threshold.
</P>
<P>
Units traded fell from 1.3 million last Friday to 660,000.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Airways was Monday's main feature with 345,000 shares
sold at between 8.50 Shillings and 9.15 Shillings. Out of these,
some 265,000 units were moved on the three-day special counter by
foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the commercial and services counter accounted for
the highest quantum of traded volume - at 61 percent with 400,000
shares transacted.
</P>
<P>
On the same counter, the Nation Media Group went up to 150
Shillings before easing to 142 Shillings on 2,200 shares. Express
Kenya climbed to 36.75 Shillings on 450 shares while Uchumi was
steady at 45 Shillings for 22, 300 shares.  
</P>
